## Ticket Orchestrator Justification

### Result Preview (REQUIRED)

Before explaining your reasoning, describe **what you plan to return**:
- How many ticket agent requests you will dispatch
- For each request: which ticket it implements, the key details included, and the file paths
- The execution ordering and why
- Any tickets you chose NOT to dispatch (and why)

### Justification

Structure your justification around:
1. **Ticket-to-Request Mapping**: Whether you created exactly one agent request per ticket — no more, no fewer — the controller will verify 1:1 mapping
2. **Request Completeness**: Whether each request includes full ticket details (ID, title, description, tasks, acceptance criteria, file references) so the agent can work independently
3. **Ordering**: Whether the dispatch order respects ticket dependencies — the controller will check against the dependency graph
4. **Plan Fidelity**: Whether you faithfully translated the plan without collapsing, splitting, or reinterpreting tickets
5. **Assumptions**: What you assume about ticket independence or execution context that the controller should verify
